710295f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 155th Street (West)
710295f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue, at West 155th Street, viewing northeastward
across the ''El'' station there, to the Bronx side of the
Harlem River. At the left is the Polo Grounds. Crossing
the River at about 158th Street, is the New York and Putnam
Railroad Bridge. The photographers vantage point is the
viaduct forming 155th Street.
June 5, 1940
No's. 1-2-3
P. L. Sperr

710291f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 155th Street (West)
710291f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue, at West 155th Street, showing various
aspects of this locale. View No. 1 is northward along
the line of the Avenue showing the ''El'' trains there-
upon. At the left is the baseball park, the Polo Grounds.
View No. 2 is eastward showing the viaduct carrying 155th
Street over this point. In the background is the Bronx
shore of the Parlem River. Beyond the 155th Street Bridge
appears the super structures of the Yankee Stadium and
the new Borough Hall Building. No. 3 is limited to the
viaduct entranoes to the ''E1'' at the left and the Street
at the right. The view is northward. Note High Bridge
is the distance.
June 5, 1940
No's. 1-2-3
